The paper discusses the use of recurrent neural networks with LSTM units to evaluate short computer programs, which falls under the domain of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves training neural networks, which falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing and character-level representations, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-categories.
